node.title: Man wanted in relation to Auckland shooting investigation found
node.description: A 24-year-old man sought in relation to an Auckland shooting last month has been found by police.
node.content:
["A 24-year-old man sought in relation to an Auckland shooting last month has been found by police.", "", "
Photo: 123rf.com
", "Five people were hurt near the Sandringham Road Extension, in the suburb of Mt Roskill, on 11 March after shots were fired into a car park. None of the injuries were life-threatening.", "Police said they still wanted to hear from anyone who knew the man whose photo was published on 31 March 2022.", "", "
Photo: NZ Police
", "Anyone who was in the area and has information can call police on 105, quoting file number 220312/6041, or Operation Grizzly, or anonymously via Crime Stoppers on 0800 555 111.", "Two people have already been arrested as part of the investigation into the shooting dubbed Operation Grizzly."]
